            <thetext>The IFormElement Interface lacks on a &quot;resetValue&quot; method. This method is important for e.g. resetting a whole form with several form elements.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>7459</commentid>
            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2009-01-27 17:06:08 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Concerning the SelectBox widget (and also other form widgets):
It would be helpful to offer a possibility to set a kind of user default to which the widget falls back when a &quot;resetValue&quot; is called.

Maybe we need an additional API for this to offer a default value for each of the form widgets. If no default value is set then we can fall back to e.g. empty string (for textField widgets) or the first element (for selectBox widgets).</thetext>
          </long_desc>
